com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel

Class GModelFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel.GModelFactory

  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public final class GModelFactory
extends java.lang.Object

    With Untyped ModelFactory

    GModelFactory provides creation helper method for GIModelFactories, which has no other binding to any generated BswmdModel. If you need only untyped instance, you could simple call the createFactory(IGeneratorPackageReferable) method to get a new ModelFactory for a generator.

      • createFactory

        @PublishedMethod
public static GIModelFactory createFactory(IProjectContext projectContext,
                                                             IHasValidationOrigin validationResultOrigin)
        Creates a new GIModelFactory instance, which could be used to instantiate many BswmdModels, in different variants.

        Untyped BswmdModel without an IGeneratorPackage (e.g. old automation use case)

        The BswmdModel also supports the use case without a generator. The method createFactory (IProjectContext, IHasValidationOrigin) can create a ModelFactory with no binding to a generator ( IGeneratorPackage). Such a model could be used for example in the Automation interface.

        Note: The IHasValidationOrigin instance is used for IValidationResult creation, when an incorrect access is made in the BswmdModel.

        You could create an IHasValidationOrigin by using the ValidatorResultOriginBuilder. 

         
  IHasValidationOrigin origin = ValidatorResultOriginBuilder.createOrigin("MyMsn","MyComponent");

  GIModelFactory modelFactory = GModelFactory.createFactory(getProjectContext(), origin);

  //Use the modelFactory as the "normal" factory.
        Parameters:
        projectContext - the IProjectContext
        validationResultOrigin - The Validation resultOrigin.
        Returns:
        the GI model factory
